title: [Library, East Wing]
description: Floor to ceiling bookcases line the eastern and western walls at this section of the library, each shelf packed tightly with volumes and tomes.  A tall window neatly bisects the eastern wall and is lined with a deep window seat.  Plump blue cushions adorned with white piping lay in neat piles to the right of the seat while a pair of three-tiered bookcases divide the room in half and are lined with past issues of the Elanthian Times.
